{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2c7928a-f275-471f-8bc8-eff748e060a9","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet, but here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a dotnet tool:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n\n  <!-- Makes it a dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server using stdio transport</Description>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n  <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/you/repo</RepositoryUrl>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Key properties:**\n\n| Property | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `PackAsTool` | Marks the project as a .NET tool |\n| `ToolCommandName` | The CLI command users invoke |\n| `PackageId` | The NuGet package identifier |\n\n**Publish steps:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet pack -c Release\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_KEY --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Users install with:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install --global MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # runs via stdio\n```\n\nMake sure your `Main` method reads from stdin/writes to stdout for the stdio transport — no console logging to stdout that would interfere with MCP framing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3032894d-4807-4b1d-8273-4ec31ac2801b","outputTokens":458,"requestId":"2C04:2B537A:29A1B08:2E05D9B:69FD3725"},"id":"a6f40ec6-3864-4478-8b3f-77d6e1dec484","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:06:54.270Z","parentId":"0ab58d4f-8cd8-4ffa-9db8-09e4ffb92687"}
